  "prompt": "Can I send 500 and 1000 rs cash notes to India through USPS mail from USA?",
  "response": "Sending cash through international mail, including using USPS, is generally not recommended and may even be prohibited by postal regulations. It's important to check both the USPS guidelines and the import regulations of the destination country, in this case, India.\n\nFor India specifically, sending Indian currency notes, especially the denominations of \u20b9500 and \u20b91000 that were demonetized in 2016, is problematic. These notes are no longer legal tender in India, and attempting to send cash, particularly in these forms, could lead to issues with customs.\n\nIf you need to transfer money to India, it's advisable to use more secure and reliable methods such as bank transfers, online money transfer services like Western Union, or financial platforms that ensure compliance with international regulations. Always consult the latest postal regulations and guidelines from the respective postal services and customs authorities before sending cash or any valuable items internationally.",
